 \\$600 for 7 years at a rate of 1.5\\% per year simple interest.\n\nCalculate the total interest earned during the 7 years.","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"calculate"},{"id":"0580-2021MayJune-Paper23-Q06","paper":"2021MayJune-Paper23","qnum":6,"marks":2,"topics":["Number"],"s":"1.6","d":2,"cat":"number","topic":"The four operations","qtype":"four operations","g":"mixed","src":"0580/23/M/J/21 Q06","year":2021,"session":"MayJune","tex":"Maria buys $n$ pencils that cost $p$ cents each.\\\\\nShe pays with a \\$$y$ note.\n\nFind, in terms of $n$, $p$ and $y$, the amount of change Maria receives.\\\\\nGive your answer in cents.","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"find"},{"id":"0580-2021MayJune-Paper23-Q07","paper":"2021MayJune-Paper23","qnum":7,"marks":2,"topics":["Number","Mensuration"],"s":"1.3","d":2,"cat":"number","topic":"Powers and roots","qtype":"powers and roots","g":"indices","src":"0580/23/M/J/21 Q07","year":2021,"session":"MayJune","tex":"\\[12 \\qquad 18 \\qquad 29 \\qquad 49 \\qquad 91 \\qquad 125\\]\n\nFrom the list of numbers, write down\n\n(a) a cube number,\n\n(b) a prime number.","parts":[{"label":"(a)","marks":1},{"label":"(b)","marks":1}],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"recall","cmd":"write"},{"id":"0580-2021MayJune-Paper23-Q08","paper":"2021MayJune-Paper23","qnum":8,"marks":2,"topics":["Number"],"s":"1.16","d":2,"cat":"number","topic":"Money","qtype":"money and currency","g":"mixed","src":"0580/23/M/J/21 Q08","year":2021,"session":"MayJune","tex":"Alex changes 190 euros (\\euro) into pounds (£) when £1 = \\euro 1.1723.\n\nCalculate the amount Alex receives.\\\\\nGive your answer correct to 2 decimal places.","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"calculate"},{"id":"0580-2021MayJune-Paper23-Q09","paper":"2021MayJune-Paper23","qnum":9,"marks":3,"topics":["Number"],"s":"1.4","d":2,"cat":"number","topic":"Fractions, decimals, percentages","qtype":"fractions, decimals, percentages","g":"mixed","src":"0580/23/M/J/21 Q09","year":2021,"session":"MayJune","tex":"**Without using a calculator**, work out $1\\dfrac{2}{3} \\div 7\\dfrac{1}{2}$.\n\nYou must show all your working and give your answer as a fraction in its simplest form.","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"calculate"},{"id":"0580-2021MayJune-Paper23-Q10","paper":"2021MayJune-Paper23","qnum":10,"marks":4,"topics":["Number","Geometry","Transformations and vectors"],"s":"1.1","d":2,"cat":"number","topic":"Types of number","qtype":"types of number","g":"mixed","src":"0580/23/M/J/21 Q10","year":2021,"session":"MayJune","tex":"(a) Describe fully the **single** transformation that maps triangle $T$ onto triangle $A$.\n\n(b) Draw the image of triangle $T$ after an enlargement, scale factor $-\\dfrac{1}{2}$, centre $(0, 0)$.","parts":[{"label":"(a)","marks":2},{"label":"(b)","marks":2}],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"recall","cmd":"describe"},{"id":"0580-2021MayJune-Paper23-Q11","paper":"2021MayJune-Paper23","qnum":11,"marks":2,"topics":["Algebra and graphs"],"s":"2.2","d":2,"cat":"algebra","topic":"Algebraic manipulation","qtype":"algebraic manipulation","g":"mixed","src":"0580/23/M/J/21 Q11","year":2021,"session":"MayJune","tex":"Simplify $3x^3 \\times 4x^4$.","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"recall","cmd":"simplify"},{"id":"0580-2021MayJune-Paper23-Q12","paper":"2021MayJune-Paper23","qnum":12,"marks":2,"topics":["Number"],"s":"1.1","d":2,"cat":"number","topic":"Types of number","qtype":"types of number","g":"mixed","src":"0580/23/M/J/21 Q12","year":2021,"session":"MayJune","tex":"$x$ is an integer and $-3 \\leqslant 2x - 1 < 3$.\n\nFind the values of $x$.","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"find"},{"id":"0580-2021MayJune-Paper23-Q13","paper":"2021MayJune-Paper23","qnum":13,"marks":2,"topics":["Algebra and graphs"],"s":"2.2","d":2,"cat":"algebra","topic":"Algebraic manipulation","qtype":"algebraic manipulation","g":"mixed","src":"0580/23/M/J/21 Q13","year":2021,"session":"MayJune","tex":"Expand and simplify.\n\\[6(t-q) - 2(t-3q)\\]","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"recall","cmd":"simplify"},{"id":"0580-2021MayJune-Paper23-Q14","paper":"2021MayJune-Paper23","qnum":14,"marks":3,"topics":["Transformations and vectors"],"s":"7.3","d":2,"cat":"vectors","topic":"Magnitude of a vector","qtype":"magnitude and unit vectors","g":"mixed","src":"0580/23/M/J/21 Q14","year":2021,"session":"MayJune","tex":"The magnitude of the vector $\\begin{pmatrix} 20 \\\\ k \\end{pmatrix}$ is 29.\n\nFind the value of $k$.","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"find"},{"id":"0580-2021MayJune-Paper23-Q15","paper":"2021MayJune-Paper23","qnum":15,"marks":6,"topics":["Coordinate geometry","Geometry","Mensuration"],"s":"3.6","d":2,"cat":"coord","topic":"Parallel lines","qtype":"parallel lines","g":"mixed","src":"0580/23/M/J/21 Q15","year":2021,"session":"MayJune","tex":"In the diagram, $AB$ is parallel to $CD$.\\\\\n$AD$ and $BC$ intersect at $X$.\\\\\n$AB = 6$\\,cm, $CD = 12$\\,cm, $CX = 8$\\,cm and $DX = 7$\\,cm.\n\n(a) Complete the statement.\n\nTriangle $ABX$ is  to triangle $DCX$.\n\n(b) Work out the length of $BX$.\n\n(c) The area of triangle $DCX$ is 26.906\\,cm$^2$.\n\nUse this value to find the area of\n\n(i)  triangle $ABX$,\n\n triangle $ACX$.","parts":[{"label":"(a)","marks":1},{"label":"(b)","marks":2},{"label":"(c)","marks":2}],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"complete"},{"id":"0580-2021MayJune-Paper23-Q16","paper":"2021MayJune-Paper23","qnum":16,"marks":2,"topics":["Number","Geometry","Mensuration"],"s":"1.10","d":2,"cat":"number","topic":"Limits of accuracy","qtype":"limits of accuracy","g":"mixed","src":"0580/23/M/J/21 Q16","year":2021,"session":"MayJune","tex":"The sides of a regular hexagon are 80\\,mm, correct to the nearest millimetre.\n\nCalculate the lower bound of the perimeter of the hexagon.","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"calculate"},{"id":"0580-2021MayJune-Paper23-Q17","paper":"2021MayJune-Paper23","qnum":17,"marks":2,"topics":["Geometry"],"s":"4.6","d":2,"cat":"geometry","topic":"Angles","qtype":"angle calculations","g":"mixed","src":"0580/23/M/J/21 Q17","year":2021,"session":"MayJune","tex":"The interior angle of a regular polygon is $175°$.\n\nCalculate the number of sides.","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"calculate"},{"id":"0580-2021MayJune-Paper23-Q18","paper":"2021MayJune-Paper23","qnum":18,"marks":3,"topics":["Number"],"s":"1.12","d":2,"cat":"number","topic":"Rates","qtype":"rates","g":"mixed","src":"0580/23/M/J/21 Q18","year":2021,"session":"MayJune","tex":"A car starts from rest and accelerates at a rate of 3\\,m/s$^2$ for 4 seconds.\\\\\nThe car then travels at a constant speed for 10 seconds.\n\nThe diagram shows the speed--time graph for this journey.\n\n(a) Find the value of $V$.\n\n(b) Calculate the total distance travelled by the car during the 14 seconds.","parts":[{"label":"(a)","marks":1},{"label":"(b)","marks":2}],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"calculate"},{"id":"0580-2021MayJune-Paper23-Q19","paper":"2021MayJune-Paper23","qnum":19,"marks":5,"topics":["Coordinate geometry","Geometry","Trigonometry"],"s":"3.1","d":2,"cat":"coord","topic":"Coordinates","qtype":"coordinates reading/plotting","g":"graph","src":"0580/23/M/J/21 Q19","year":2021,"session":"MayJune","tex":"(a) \n$P$, $Q$ and $T$ are points on a circle.\\\\\n$ATB$ is a tangent to the circle at $T$ and $PT = PQ$.\n\nFind angle $TPQ$.\n\n(b) \nThe diagram shows a cyclic quadrilateral with an exterior angle of $68°$.\n\nFind the value of $w$ and the value of $x$.","parts":[{"label":"(a)","marks":2},{"label":"(b)","marks":3}],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"find"},{"id":"0580-2021MayJune-Paper23-Q20","paper":"2021MayJune-Paper23","qnum":20,"marks":2,"topics":["Number","Algebra and graphs"],"s":"2.2","d":2,"cat":"algebra","topic":"Algebraic manipulation","qtype":"algebraic manipulation","g":"mixed","src":"0580/23/M/J/21 Q20","year":2021,"session":"MayJune","tex":"Simplify $2.1 \\times 10^p + 2.1 \\times 10^{p-1}$.\\\\\nGive your answer in standard form.","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"recall","cmd":"simplify"},{"id":"0580-2021MayJune-Paper23-Q21","paper":"2021MayJune-Paper23","qnum":21,"marks":3,"topics":["Coordinate geometry","Geometry"],"s":"3.1","d":2,"cat":"coord","topic":"Coordinates","qtype":"coordinates reading/plotting","g":"graph","src":"0580/23/M/J/21 Q21","year":2021,"session":"MayJune","tex":"The shortest distance from $B$ to $AC$ is 12.8\\,cm.\n\nCalculate $BC$.","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"calculate"},{"id":"0580-2021MayJune-Paper23-Q22","paper":"2021MayJune-Paper23","qnum":22,"marks":2,"topics":["Algebra and graphs"],"s":"2.8","d":2,"cat":"algebra","topic":"Proportion","qtype":"proportion","g":"proportion","src":"0580/23/M/J/21 Q22","year":2021,"session":"MayJune","tex":"$z$ is inversely proportional to the square of $(y-2)$.\\\\\nWhen $y = 5$, $z = 9$.\n\nFind $z$ in terms of $y$.","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"find"},{"id":"0580-2021MayJune-Paper23-Q23","paper":"2021MayJune-Paper23","qnum":23,"marks":4,"topics":["Geometry"],"s":"4.6","d":2,"cat":"geometry","topic":"Angles","qtype":"angle calculations","g":"mixed","src":"0580/23/M/J/21 Q23","year":2021,"session":"MayJune","tex":"A triangle has sides of length 11\\,cm, 10\\,cm and 9\\,cm.\n\nCalculate the largest angle in the triangle.","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"calculate"},{"id":"0580-2021MayJune-Paper23-Q24","paper":"2021MayJune-Paper23","qnum":24,"marks":4,"topics":["Algebra and graphs"],"s":"2.11","d":2,"cat":"algebra","topic":"Sketching curves","qtype":"sketching curves","g":"graph","src":"0580/23/M/J/21 Q24","year":2021,"session":"MayJune","tex":"On the axes, sketch the graph of each of these functions.\n\n(a) $y = \\dfrac{2}{x}$\n\n(b) $y = 2^{-x}$","parts":[{"label":"(a)","marks":2},{"label":"(b)","marks":2}],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"recall","cmd":"sketch"},{"id":"0580-2021MayJune-Paper23-Q25","paper":"2021MayJune-Paper23","qnum":25,"marks":4,"topics":["Algebra and graphs","Coordinate geometry"],"s":"2.8","d":2,"cat":"algebra","topic":"Proportion","qtype":"proportion","g":"proportion","src":"0580/23/M/J/21 Q25","year":2021,"session":"MayJune","tex":"Find the $x$-coordinates of the points on the graph of $y = x^5 - 5x^4$ where the gradient is 0.","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"find"},{"id":"0580-2021MayJune-Paper23-Q26","paper":"2021MayJune-Paper23","qnum":26,"marks":3,"topics":["Probability"],"s":"8.3","d":2,"cat":"probability","topic":"Combined events","qtype":"combined events","g":"mixed","src":"0580/23/M/J/21 Q26","year":2021,"session":"MayJune","tex":"Malik goes to a shop every day to buy bread.\n\nOn any day, the probability that Malik goes to the shop in the morning is 0.7.\\\\\nIf he goes in the morning, the probability that there is bread for Malik to buy is 0.95.\\\\\nIf he goes later, the probability that there is bread for Malik to buy is 0.6.\n\nCalculate the probability that, on any day, there is bread for Malik to buy.","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"calculate"}]